				Who Knows Best? (Dis)agreement on Reported Participation of Women in Intra-Household Decision-Making
			</h3>

			<p class="font-medium text-gray-400 mb-4">
				Kasturi Kandalam and Rosa Abraham
			</p>

			<p class="leading-relaxed">
				This research examines discrepancies between spouses' reports on women's participation in household decision-making using nationally representative data from India. We document systematic patterns of disagreement across different types of decisions and explore their determinants and implications for measuring women's empowerment.
			</p>
